WEBVTT

00:05.172 --> 00:06.507
[Catherine]
<i>Previously on</i> The Spanish Princess...

00:06.540 --> 00:08.042
[Catherine] God save the King.

00:08.075 --> 00:11.011
<i>Your father passed</i>
<i>into God's mercy, Your Grace.</i>

00:11.045 --> 00:14.482
-Maggie, I will see you freed from here.
-You have no power, Catherine.

00:14.515 --> 00:16.183
<i>We are at the mercy of the Tudors.</i>

00:16.217 --> 00:17.485
[Oviedo] <i>Lina, I ask you this--</i>

00:17.518 --> 00:21.255
that you will pledge yourself to me
and our new family.

00:21.288 --> 00:24.358
[Henry] <i>I've made a marriage plan</i>
<i>for my sister, Princess Mary.</i>

00:24.392 --> 00:28.462
And Charles, who is to be your husband,
is my Spanish nephew.

00:28.496 --> 00:29.530
A pardon.

00:29.563 --> 00:32.099
You may return to court
with all your children.

00:32.133 --> 00:33.267
<i>You will be looked after.</i>

00:33.300 --> 00:34.635
[Oviedo] <i>The army marches out to Kent.</i>

00:34.668 --> 00:37.238
<i>I go with them and then</i>
<i>perhaps to war in France.</i>

00:37.271 --> 00:38.339
[Catherine] <i>I love you.</i>

00:38.372 --> 00:40.074
Harry, tell me what my fate shall be.

00:40.107 --> 00:42.243
[Margaret] <i>The Spanish girl</i>
<i>will destroy us all.</i>

00:42.276 --> 00:44.478
If Harry marries her, he is cursed.

00:44.512 --> 00:46.514
<i>No boys, no heirs.</i>

00:46.547 --> 00:48.082
[Henry] <i>We do not fear the morrow.</i>

00:48.115 --> 00:51.385
We make it as king and wife.

00:51.419 --> 00:54.422
[lively music]

00:54.455 --> 00:59.460
♪ ♪

01:41.469 --> 01:44.438
[quiet music]

01:44.472 --> 01:49.477
♪ ♪

02:18.472 --> 02:20.441
Your... Your Grace?

02:23.477 --> 02:26.413
If my father is to visit...

02:26.447 --> 02:28.382
I will wear the most precious one.

02:30.317 --> 02:33.554
Bessie, bring the crown.

02:33.587 --> 02:36.557
[upbeat string music]

02:36.590 --> 02:37.691
♪ ♪

02:37.725 --> 02:40.728
-Your Grace.
-Good evening, Your Grace.

02:40.761 --> 02:42.596
Chaplain Wolsey.

02:42.630 --> 02:47.635
♪ ♪

02:51.405 --> 02:54.375
[uneasy music]

02:54.408 --> 02:55.910
♪ ♪

02:55.943 --> 02:57.778
Unhand me at once.

02:57.811 --> 03:00.180
♪ ♪

03:00.214 --> 03:02.850
How dare you touch your queen?

03:02.883 --> 03:05.853
[tense music]

03:05.886 --> 03:10.891
♪ ♪

03:30.611 --> 03:32.546
This is an outrage.

03:32.580 --> 03:34.982
[man] No, the outrage...

03:35.215 --> 03:38.252
is that you've been
too many hours away from me.

03:38.285 --> 03:39.587
A queen must ready

03:39.620 --> 03:41.855
for the King of Spain's arrival.

03:41.889 --> 03:44.858
[tender music]

03:44.892 --> 03:49.863
♪ ♪

03:49.897 --> 03:54.802
Her lips are moving,
but I cannot hear a word.

03:54.835 --> 03:57.504
Take care, my lord...

03:57.538 --> 03:59.940
or you may lose your kingship.

04:01.575 --> 04:03.911
I think you'd be more upset
than I if that fate

04:03.944 --> 04:05.613
should befall me.

04:05.646 --> 04:06.814
♪ ♪

04:06.847 --> 04:08.616
[knife clatters]

04:08.649 --> 04:13.654
♪ ♪

04:20.394 --> 04:22.529
[gasps, laughs]

04:22.563 --> 04:27.568
♪ ♪

04:50.491 --> 04:53.460
[serene orchestral music]

04:53.494 --> 04:56.330
♪ ♪

04:56.363 --> 04:58.899
[parrot squawks]

05:00.901 --> 05:03.437
He is here, your father.

05:03.470 --> 05:05.472
The last steps will be delicate,

05:05.506 --> 05:08.676
but I have made a vow to Henry,
and I will deliver on it.

05:08.709 --> 05:10.577
[Lina] Oviedo will be glad.

05:10.611 --> 05:12.980
The troops are tired
of waiting at the coast.

05:13.013 --> 05:16.083
The French have felt the heat of our gaze,

05:16.316 --> 05:20.087
but if my father joins us, and we sail,
then they will feel our weapons.

05:21.889 --> 05:23.691
[Lina] Oh...

05:23.724 --> 05:26.593
Maggie, I will take him now.

05:26.627 --> 05:30.764
Oh, hello, my handsome prince.

05:30.798 --> 05:32.700
My little jewel, Henry.

05:32.733 --> 05:35.102
Come, meet your tricky <i>abuelo.</i>

05:35.335 --> 05:38.105
[dramatic music]

05:38.338 --> 05:43.343
♪ ♪

05:44.712 --> 05:47.681
[indistinct chatter]

05:47.715 --> 05:51.919
♪ ♪

05:51.952 --> 05:53.020
[Maggie] Ursula.

05:53.053 --> 05:54.822
Lady mother, here.

05:54.855 --> 05:55.956
Henry.

05:55.989 --> 05:59.393
[chatter continues]

05:59.426 --> 06:02.062
Reggie, we're going to meet
Catherine's father,

06:02.096 --> 06:03.497
the King of Spain.

06:03.530 --> 06:05.032
Well, he's only king
because he stole the crown

06:05.065 --> 06:08.402
from his daughter, Joanna,
and threw her in the madhouse.

06:08.435 --> 06:09.937
Princess Mary.

06:09.970 --> 06:13.741
Well, next it will belong to you.

06:13.774 --> 06:15.743
[door opens]

06:18.579 --> 06:21.548
[sweeping orchestral music]

06:21.582 --> 06:26.587
♪ ♪

06:34.394 --> 06:35.662
Oh, heavens.

06:35.696 --> 06:38.532
Is that who I've been betrothed
to all this time?

06:38.565 --> 06:40.934
You could slice bread with that chin.

06:40.968 --> 06:43.470
Look how rich his clothes are, Mary.

06:43.504 --> 06:45.405
You could bathe in gold.

06:45.439 --> 06:49.743
His Imperial Highness,
King Ferdinand of Aragon and Castile,

06:49.777 --> 06:53.714
and his heir and grandson,
Charles of Burgundy.

06:53.747 --> 06:56.750
We present to you the English court.

06:56.784 --> 07:00.053
Your Graces, welcome.

07:00.087 --> 07:04.792
♪ ♪

07:04.825 --> 07:06.994
[crowd murmuring, laughter]

07:07.027 --> 07:11.131
♪ ♪

07:11.165 --> 07:16.770
[in Spanish] Welcome
to Westminster Palace, I am Princess Mary.

07:22.476 --> 07:24.444
I believe you are to be my husband.

07:24.478 --> 07:26.780
♪ ♪

07:26.814 --> 07:28.882
[in English]
Where is Katalina?

07:28.916 --> 07:31.885
[upbeat string music]

07:31.919 --> 07:36.924
♪ ♪

08:00.981 --> 08:03.951
[fanfare playing]

08:03.984 --> 08:08.989
♪ ♪

08:12.626 --> 08:14.728
Behold...

08:14.761 --> 08:16.797
my son and heir,

08:16.830 --> 08:19.700
the future king of England,

08:19.733 --> 08:21.201
Henry IX!

08:21.235 --> 08:24.238
[cheers and applause]

08:29.810 --> 08:32.079
We welcome our Spanish guests,

08:32.112 --> 08:35.849
my father, King Ferdinand,
my nephew Charles.

08:35.883 --> 08:39.119
We hope that soon you will be
England's family, too.

08:39.152 --> 08:40.721
King "Henary."

08:40.754 --> 08:41.989
We meet.

08:46.994 --> 08:49.263
[Henry] Welcome to our court.

08:49.296 --> 08:52.065
We hope before too many suns have set

08:52.099 --> 08:55.636
that we'll seal a Holy League
between our two great nations

08:55.669 --> 08:56.803
and avenge the Pope

08:56.837 --> 08:59.773
for the lands the French
have stolen from him.

08:59.806 --> 09:03.210
Together, we will have war against France.

09:03.243 --> 09:06.280
But first, we eat.

09:06.313 --> 09:10.150
[applause]

09:10.183 --> 09:13.287
We have this <i>pescado...</i>

09:13.320 --> 09:14.588
but bigger.

09:14.621 --> 09:17.090
[chuckles, snaps fingers]

09:17.124 --> 09:19.960
I bring sugared grapes for you,

09:19.993 --> 09:21.628
your favorite.

09:23.597 --> 09:26.199
Remember?

09:26.233 --> 09:28.068
Take one.

09:28.101 --> 09:31.204
[uneasy music]

09:31.238 --> 09:34.174
Please, enjoy our... Camelot.

09:37.010 --> 09:39.980
[band playing]

09:40.013 --> 09:42.716
♪ ♪

09:42.749 --> 09:44.918
-He's shorter than I imagined.
-[chuckles]

09:44.952 --> 09:46.954
He is challenged by you.

09:46.987 --> 09:49.923
You should take it as a compliment.

09:49.957 --> 09:54.962
♪ ♪

10:02.669 --> 10:06.606
[in Spanish] Charles, when we are wed
and you are King of Spain,

10:06.640 --> 10:11.078
will we rule together
like my brother and Queen Catherine?

10:12.846 --> 10:14.047
If my lady wishes it.

10:15.782 --> 10:17.884
My lady wishes for more wine.

10:19.219 --> 10:21.321
My Princess.

10:21.355 --> 10:25.058
♪ ♪

10:25.092 --> 10:28.762
[in English]
A young mischief and mystery.

10:28.795 --> 10:30.230
[Brandon] There's no mystery in Mary.

10:30.263 --> 10:32.366
Mm, she acts giddy,
but she can play the role

10:32.399 --> 10:33.934
in seven languages.

10:33.967 --> 10:36.069
I'm quite sure of it.

10:36.103 --> 10:38.405
Uh, Thomas...

10:38.638 --> 10:43.043
a scholar, statesman,
educator, and great intellect.

10:43.076 --> 10:47.314
Mary, he will best you,
so do not even try to take him on.

10:47.347 --> 10:49.950
I wouldn't dream of it.

10:49.983 --> 10:52.853
[Brandon chuckles]

10:52.886 --> 10:54.821
♪ ♪

10:54.855 --> 10:57.424
-I'm Thomas More.
-Lady Margaret Pole.

10:57.657 --> 10:59.059
[More] Pleasure.

10:59.092 --> 11:00.227
I've recently had the honor

11:00.260 --> 11:02.162
of being appointed
undersheriff to the King.

11:02.195 --> 11:04.431
Your reputation goes before you.

11:04.664 --> 11:07.267
Is it true you nearly left the law
to take religious orders?

11:07.300 --> 11:11.204
I did. I spent a happy year
with Carthusian monks outside the city,

11:11.238 --> 11:14.808
but, alas, it was not my calling.

11:14.841 --> 11:16.676
♪ ♪

11:16.710 --> 11:19.713
[applause]

11:21.782 --> 11:23.283
Excuse me.

11:25.919 --> 11:29.056
Are we the center of the world, Charlie?

11:29.089 --> 11:30.757
Of course we are.

11:32.192 --> 11:34.861
A shame that Meg is not here, then.

11:34.895 --> 11:36.963
I'm sure your sister's having
a splendid time

11:36.997 --> 11:39.099
with her dashing Scottish king.

11:40.400 --> 11:43.403
[children yelling,
items clattering, dog barking]

11:45.872 --> 11:48.842
[stately music]

11:48.875 --> 11:53.780
♪ ♪

11:54.181 --> 11:56.850
Come on, sit up. You haven't finished yet.

11:56.883 --> 11:58.919
Uh, no. Stop it.

11:58.952 --> 12:01.488
Food is for eating and not throwing.

12:01.721 --> 12:03.256
[James] Ah, my love!

12:04.157 --> 12:06.860
What a perfect sight you all make.

12:06.893 --> 12:10.497
[Meg] James, your son is throwing food.

12:10.730 --> 12:11.932
[James] Ah, he's a boy!

12:11.965 --> 12:14.201
I'll not have his wings clipped
by a woman.

12:14.234 --> 12:15.368
[soft music playing]

12:15.402 --> 12:18.772
I told you not to make gunpowder
when you're drunk.

12:18.805 --> 12:21.808
That is not clipping your wings.
It's saving your life.

12:21.842 --> 12:26.213
Well, if we don't try our hand at science,
we'll never learn anything new, hen, eh?

12:26.246 --> 12:28.915
[music stops]

12:28.949 --> 12:31.284
Will you tend to them?

12:31.318 --> 12:34.221
How much do I look like a queen to you?

12:34.254 --> 12:36.790
I'm covered in the mess of your children.

12:36.823 --> 12:38.425
Remind me again,
how many of them are mine?

12:38.458 --> 12:40.293
Oh, yes, just two.

12:40.327 --> 12:41.862
Aye.

12:41.895 --> 12:45.499
Precious they are, too,
my love, the ones that lived.

12:45.532 --> 12:47.767
[soft music playing]

12:47.801 --> 12:49.402
While Catherine, Queen of England--

12:49.436 --> 12:53.039
Negasi, will you stop playing, please?

12:53.073 --> 12:55.876
It soothes the soul, Your Grace.

12:57.477 --> 13:00.113
Catherine writes that her father
is visiting London

13:00.147 --> 13:04.284
and all of Christendom celebrates her
for the pact she is negotiating

13:04.317 --> 13:07.154
between England, Spain, and Burgundy.

13:07.187 --> 13:10.056
Even the Pope has praised her for it.

13:12.025 --> 13:14.161
James...

13:15.562 --> 13:17.397
What is that?

13:17.430 --> 13:19.299
[James] Teeth.

13:19.332 --> 13:23.036
That's a Douglas,
and that one's a Stewart.

13:23.069 --> 13:26.540
If they're gonna kill each other,
they may as well be used for science.

13:28.909 --> 13:30.877
Catherine unites.

13:30.911 --> 13:33.313
We should do the same with the clans.

13:33.346 --> 13:36.550
Ah, even the Bruce
found that tough weather.

13:36.583 --> 13:39.886
That's why England lords it over us.

13:39.920 --> 13:44.057
My brother sent me here to make the peace
between our countries, and we have that.

13:45.225 --> 13:48.195
And if Catherine can engage
in the running of her country,

13:48.228 --> 13:49.396
so can I.

13:53.266 --> 13:56.970
Stick to what you're good at--
keeping house and raising bairns.

13:57.003 --> 13:59.539
[dramatic music]

13:59.573 --> 14:02.108
[indistinct chatter]

14:02.142 --> 14:08.181
[in Spanish] These English lied to you
and cast you out. They starved you.

14:08.949 --> 14:12.519
It was the King's grandmother,
Lady Margaret, who stood against me,

14:12.552 --> 14:14.087
and she is gone.

14:14.120 --> 14:17.224
Yet here you are. By God's will
and your own, you have endured,

14:17.257 --> 14:18.425
and now you are their Queen.

14:18.925 --> 14:21.094
[applause]

14:21.127 --> 14:24.531
[indistinct chatter]

14:24.564 --> 14:28.101
[in English] I wish for Spain and England
to be strong together.

14:28.134 --> 14:31.204
This French campaign against the Pope
must be defeated.

14:31.238 --> 14:34.107
If we unite, we can achieve that.

14:34.140 --> 14:38.178
You wish to make war with France
for the sake of the Pope,

14:38.211 --> 14:40.580
or maybe you want to win back
your own land?

14:40.614 --> 14:43.283
France could be another golden ball

14:43.316 --> 14:46.953
to ornament your Camelot.

14:46.987 --> 14:49.656
You cannot countenance
the actions of the French.

14:49.889 --> 14:53.026
Seizing lands so close to Rome,
it's an insult to the papacy.

14:53.059 --> 14:55.262
It is an outrage, and my mother
would've ridden out already.

14:55.295 --> 14:58.565
Your mother knew war
like she knew the Eucharist,

14:58.598 --> 15:00.533
but you, "Henary,"

15:00.567 --> 15:02.335
what do you know about war?

15:02.369 --> 15:05.238
You are not a general.

15:05.272 --> 15:06.940
I've had my foundry in Greenwich

15:06.973 --> 15:09.309
forge new armor like the world
has never seen.

15:09.342 --> 15:11.378
You will be glad of it, if--

15:12.612 --> 15:15.915
when we face the French together.

15:15.949 --> 15:18.218
<i>Es la calidad,</i> Katalina.

15:18.251 --> 15:21.688
It is the quality
of the man within the metal

15:21.921 --> 15:24.057
that is the key.

15:25.458 --> 15:29.029
Well, I'll show you
both the metal of the suits

15:29.062 --> 15:30.263
and the mettle of the men who wear them.

15:30.297 --> 15:31.364
We'll have a joust.

15:34.034 --> 15:35.235
[chuckles]

15:36.636 --> 15:39.339
[dramatic music]

15:39.372 --> 15:42.309
Katalina...

15:42.342 --> 15:44.711
whose interests do you tend to,

15:44.944 --> 15:48.448
your husband's or <i>España?</i>

15:48.481 --> 15:50.383
♪ ♪

15:50.417 --> 15:53.286
Father...

15:53.320 --> 15:57.357
I am a steadfast daughter and a true wife.

15:57.390 --> 15:59.726
I am loyal to Spain and to Henry.

15:59.959 --> 16:04.964
♪ ♪

16:06.366 --> 16:09.336
[indistinct chatter]

16:09.369 --> 16:12.372
[bell tolling in the distance]

16:12.405 --> 16:17.344
♪ ♪

16:17.377 --> 16:20.347
[horse chuffs]

16:20.380 --> 16:25.385
♪ ♪

16:38.565 --> 16:40.467
[lock clicks]

16:40.500 --> 16:42.469
[clatter]

16:42.502 --> 16:46.206
♪ ♪

16:46.239 --> 16:48.475
Who is here?

16:48.508 --> 16:50.377
Should I defend myself?

16:50.410 --> 16:52.245
[gasps] Oviedo!

16:52.278 --> 16:53.747
Oh! [laughs]

16:53.780 --> 16:56.383
Allah be praised, but you smell good.

16:56.416 --> 16:58.651
Oh, I smell of mutton fat.

16:58.685 --> 17:01.221
They ate a whole farm in there tonight.

17:01.254 --> 17:03.456
Wh... why are you back from Dover?

17:03.490 --> 17:06.126
[Oviedo] General Howard.
He gives us leave.

17:06.159 --> 17:08.728
They say we will sail
and should rest before campaign,

17:08.762 --> 17:11.698
but I believe this when it happens.

17:11.731 --> 17:15.468
Mm, Catherine's father is here now
with the King and Queen.

17:15.502 --> 17:18.471
If he agrees to join them,
you will have your war.

17:18.505 --> 17:19.773
Good.

17:19.806 --> 17:21.408
[in Spanish]
Then I praise God.

17:22.308 --> 17:23.376
[in English]
You look tired.

17:23.410 --> 17:25.412
[sighs]

17:25.445 --> 17:27.313
King Henry wears out
the spirits of his men

17:27.347 --> 17:30.049
before they have even crossed into France.

17:30.083 --> 17:31.418
[Oviedo scoffs]

17:31.451 --> 17:35.121
I wonder if he even knows
how to use an army.

17:35.155 --> 17:36.456
Well...

17:38.057 --> 17:40.427
...I know how to use you.

17:40.460 --> 17:43.430
[light music]

17:43.463 --> 17:48.468
♪ ♪

17:52.639 --> 17:55.108
[both chuckle]

17:55.141 --> 18:00.146
♪ ♪

18:03.783 --> 18:05.852
[both moan]

18:06.085 --> 18:11.090
♪ ♪

18:14.594 --> 18:16.296
[cheers and applause]

18:16.329 --> 18:19.098
[dramatic drum music]

18:19.132 --> 18:22.101
[bright fanfare]

18:22.135 --> 18:27.140
♪ ♪

18:46.726 --> 18:49.796
[dramatic music]

18:49.829 --> 18:53.199
[crowd cheering]

18:53.233 --> 18:58.238
♪ ♪

19:11.317 --> 19:12.619
Can you see, Reggie?

19:17.690 --> 19:19.392
Master Pole.

19:19.425 --> 19:21.561
Master More.

19:21.594 --> 19:23.329
Lady Pole.

19:23.363 --> 19:25.932
-Uh, this is my wife, Alice.
-[Alice] Ma'am.

19:26.165 --> 19:29.202
[More] My daughters, Margaret,
Elizabeth, and Cicely.

19:29.235 --> 19:30.670
[girl] Milady.

19:32.872 --> 19:34.841
Was that book given to you
at Sheen Priory?

19:39.279 --> 19:40.847
-[More] Hmm.
-That's the most response

19:40.880 --> 19:42.282
I've had out of him all year.

19:42.315 --> 19:45.585
A silent order at such a young age,
it can take its toll.

19:47.220 --> 19:51.391
I don't wish to speak out of turn, but...

19:51.424 --> 19:53.359
he is in dire need of a tutor.

19:53.393 --> 19:55.628
I... I don't suppose you would...

19:55.662 --> 19:57.363
It would be an honor.

19:59.232 --> 20:01.467
My daughters now speak
better Latin than I do

20:01.501 --> 20:03.303
and correct me far too often.

20:03.336 --> 20:04.671
It would actually be a bit of a blessing

20:04.704 --> 20:07.473
to believe that I still
have some wisdom to impart.

20:07.507 --> 20:10.410
[chuckles]

20:10.443 --> 20:11.778
And thank you.

20:14.480 --> 20:17.483
[cheers and applause]

20:18.551 --> 20:20.553
[indistinct chatter]

20:20.587 --> 20:22.288
[rider] Lady Pole.

20:23.289 --> 20:25.491
Lady Pole...

20:25.525 --> 20:28.928
I was hoping that I may wear
your colors as I ride.

20:28.962 --> 20:30.597
-[Maggie] I don't--
-Mother...

20:30.630 --> 20:32.332
this gentleman is speaking to you.

20:32.365 --> 20:33.900
-Oh, I'm sorry.
-[lady] Lord Stafford!

20:33.933 --> 20:37.303
William Compton,
groom of the King's stool.

20:40.873 --> 20:42.475
Here, Compton.

20:42.508 --> 20:43.943
No, Henry.

20:43.977 --> 20:45.778
Be sure to win.

20:45.812 --> 20:47.513
I will tie this to my saddle.

20:49.749 --> 20:50.750
[sniffs]

20:51.818 --> 20:53.386
[Maggie chuckles]

20:53.419 --> 20:56.422
[crowd cheering]

20:58.958 --> 21:01.861
Master Brandon, may I assist the King?

21:01.894 --> 21:03.963
The King has already a squire.

21:05.665 --> 21:08.668
But you may fetch him some ale.

21:12.672 --> 21:15.642
[fanfare plays]

21:15.675 --> 21:20.680
♪ ♪

21:24.684 --> 21:28.554
[cheers and applause]

21:28.588 --> 21:32.892
[in Spanish] The young, they think
they are invincible, Katalina.

21:32.925 --> 21:34.827
[in English]
The King is invincible.

21:34.861 --> 21:37.497
[Ferdinand]
No one is invincible, Katalina,

21:37.530 --> 21:38.698
no one.

21:38.731 --> 21:40.700
This is leadership, Father.

21:40.733 --> 21:43.403
[dramatic music]

21:43.436 --> 21:46.406
[cheers and applause]

21:46.439 --> 21:51.444
♪ ♪

22:12.765 --> 22:14.901
He rides with your family emblem
on his horse.

22:14.934 --> 22:16.369
It's so romantic.

22:16.402 --> 22:17.804
[chuckles]

22:17.837 --> 22:22.775
♪ ♪

22:34.454 --> 22:35.988
[horse neighs]

22:36.022 --> 22:38.024
♪ ♪

22:38.057 --> 22:40.560
[horse chuffs]

22:40.593 --> 22:45.598
♪ ♪

23:02.115 --> 23:04.417
[Catherine breathes sharply]

23:08.087 --> 23:11.457
-[crowd cheers]
-[onlookers gasp]

23:16.596 --> 23:18.030
[man] My lord.

23:18.064 --> 23:21.033
[ominous music]

23:21.067 --> 23:22.869
♪ ♪

23:22.902 --> 23:24.070
Edward, I'm sorry.

23:24.103 --> 23:25.938
[groans]

23:25.972 --> 23:30.943
♪ ♪

23:30.977 --> 23:32.812
[breathing heavily]

23:32.845 --> 23:33.846
[yells]

23:33.880 --> 23:35.681
[both grunt]

23:35.715 --> 23:38.651
♪ ♪

23:38.684 --> 23:40.453
Bloody dogs can have it.

23:40.486 --> 23:44.991
♪ ♪

23:50.596 --> 23:52.565
Do not fret, my lady.

23:52.598 --> 23:54.667
I can still admire you with my left eye.

23:54.700 --> 23:55.968
[laughs]

23:56.002 --> 23:57.470
[sighs]

23:57.503 --> 23:59.071
Oh, can you stand?

23:59.105 --> 24:04.076
♪ ♪

24:08.614 --> 24:12.518
King Henry, unharmed in armors
from his foundry!

24:12.552 --> 24:15.021
♪ ♪

24:15.054 --> 24:17.023
I should've worn the same.

24:18.858 --> 24:22.128
[Catherine] And yet, behold Lord Stafford,

24:22.161 --> 24:25.164
born with English steel in his bones.

24:26.666 --> 24:28.034
God save the King.

24:28.067 --> 24:30.770
[all] God save the King!

24:30.803 --> 24:32.805
God save the King!

24:32.839 --> 24:34.974
[woman] God save the Queen!

24:35.007 --> 24:37.109
[all] God save the Queen!

24:39.679 --> 24:42.114
God save the Queen!

24:43.182 --> 24:45.952
[Ferdinand]
Katalina is her mother's daughter.

24:47.186 --> 24:49.522
She has convinced me.

24:49.555 --> 24:52.558
King Henry...

24:52.592 --> 24:54.927
you will have your war with France

24:54.961 --> 24:56.963
and your treaty with Spain.

24:56.996 --> 24:59.165
God be praised!

24:59.198 --> 25:01.601
[Henry] Mwah.

25:01.634 --> 25:04.070
And Charles?

25:04.103 --> 25:05.504
All of us, united?

25:05.538 --> 25:07.206
We will rise up for the Pope.

25:08.207 --> 25:11.510
You may consult
with my daughter on all matters

25:11.544 --> 25:14.614
as though you speak directly to me.

25:14.647 --> 25:16.649
She's the will of Spain.

25:16.682 --> 25:20.887
[in Spanish]
You honor me, Father, thank you.

25:20.920 --> 25:22.788
You deserve it.

25:22.822 --> 25:24.924
[rapid string music]

25:24.957 --> 25:27.627
[in English]
Tomorrow I return to Spain.

25:27.660 --> 25:29.295
We will ready for our war.

25:29.528 --> 25:31.797
♪ ♪

25:31.831 --> 25:34.800
[dramatic music]

25:34.834 --> 25:39.839
♪ ♪

25:40.773 --> 25:42.575
[Catherine] My father says
we should send troops

25:42.608 --> 25:44.911
to San Sebastian,
and he will join us there.

25:44.944 --> 25:46.178
[Howard] Sail to bloody Spain?

25:46.212 --> 25:49.181
Your Grace, we're meant
to be invading France.

25:49.215 --> 25:50.816
We only have to cross the Channel.

25:50.850 --> 25:53.886
Our aim is to deal with the French threat
to Rome, Your Grace.

25:53.920 --> 25:56.022
A resolute march southeast is needed.

25:56.055 --> 25:58.257
England has a strong claim
to the Duchy of Guyenne,

25:58.291 --> 26:00.593
which is nearby,
and we can swell our numbers there.

26:00.626 --> 26:02.161
[Henry] Aquitaine was taken by the French.

26:02.194 --> 26:06.265
Their citizens yearn
to be under English rule again.

26:06.299 --> 26:09.235
So let's give them that

26:09.268 --> 26:11.570
and land a blow to King Louis' arrogance.

26:11.604 --> 26:14.674
[Catherine] My father's army
will head north to meet us.

26:14.707 --> 26:16.275
That's good, Your Grace.

26:16.309 --> 26:18.711
My father is a boastful man.

26:18.744 --> 26:22.848
He will wish to make a grand display
of military power,

26:22.882 --> 26:27.119
and he will have that
as we march together into France.

26:27.153 --> 26:30.823
[Wolsey] You are formidable, my queen.

26:30.856 --> 26:32.992
I'm in admiration.

26:33.025 --> 26:35.995
I have worked hard to build
this treaty with my father.

26:36.028 --> 26:38.264
He appoints you his regent.

26:38.297 --> 26:40.232
It's a symbol of his trust in you.

26:40.266 --> 26:42.802
A miracle.

26:42.835 --> 26:45.972
He was jealous of my mother's strength.

26:46.005 --> 26:47.907
He could do nothing to challenge her,

26:47.940 --> 26:50.776
and so he would try to weaken
my sister and I at every turn.

26:50.810 --> 26:54.280
-Then he has changed.
-[chuckles awkwardly]

26:54.313 --> 26:55.848
When Harry...

26:57.350 --> 26:59.185
When the King wanted to marry me,

26:59.218 --> 27:02.855
my father wouldn't pay my dowry
until he needed something in return.

27:04.223 --> 27:06.659
But, yes...

27:06.692 --> 27:10.663
I think he sees me now
as worthy of respect.

27:10.696 --> 27:13.966
Perhaps he finally feels guilt
about Joanna.

27:14.000 --> 27:16.969
Your poor sister was felled
by a disorder of the mind.

27:17.003 --> 27:18.871
So my father says.

27:21.207 --> 27:23.976
The nuns of Tordesillas tend to her.

27:24.010 --> 27:27.346
You think your father put her there
to take Spain for himself.

27:29.148 --> 27:31.817
Your Grace, your father has entrusted you

27:31.851 --> 27:34.086
because he knows
that by your word and your deed,

27:34.120 --> 27:35.955
you will exalt him,

27:35.988 --> 27:39.692
as you also exalt the whole of England.

27:42.795 --> 27:45.197
Thank you...

27:45.231 --> 27:47.867
Thomas.

27:47.900 --> 27:49.201
Thank you.

27:49.235 --> 27:53.372
How wonderful to have
our trust in Spain at last.

28:00.279 --> 28:03.282
[bell tolling]

28:10.756 --> 28:13.359
He has the eyes of a hawk.

28:13.392 --> 28:15.828
He follows my every move.

28:15.861 --> 28:18.831
I count the days
until I can take him hunting.

28:20.766 --> 28:22.068
[Catherine chuckles]

28:22.101 --> 28:24.036
I love that you would feed
our son yourself.

28:24.070 --> 28:27.006
-All other princes have wet nurses.
-Mm.

28:29.141 --> 28:30.276
Thank you.

28:30.309 --> 28:32.078
You have given me so much, Catherine.

28:32.111 --> 28:33.412
Mm.

28:33.446 --> 28:36.015
Hello.

28:36.048 --> 28:39.418
I have given you
a new Spanish army to play with.

28:40.753 --> 28:42.021
I do it all for you...

28:42.054 --> 28:43.189
[baby fusses]

28:43.222 --> 28:45.991
...and for this country,

28:46.025 --> 28:47.760
for our Camelot.

28:47.793 --> 28:50.763
[dramatic music]

28:50.796 --> 28:53.999
♪ ♪

28:54.033 --> 28:57.903
Move out, to France!

28:57.937 --> 29:02.942
♪ ♪

29:04.910 --> 29:06.946
[Catherine]
And when the French are routed,

29:06.979 --> 29:11.150
the Scots will lose their wealthy patron
and be less trouble on the borders.

29:11.183 --> 29:13.119
My warrior queen.

29:13.152 --> 29:16.055
-[Catherine] Hmm.
-[horse chuffs]

29:16.088 --> 29:21.093
♪ ♪

29:26.398 --> 29:28.968
[bell tolling]

29:29.001 --> 29:30.903
[Alexander] <i>The Douglases have no respect</i>

29:30.936 --> 29:32.004
for any other clan.

29:32.037 --> 29:35.808
Your Grace, we ask for reparations
for the raids carried out

29:35.841 --> 29:38.310
by these buck-eared cocksuckers
on our Lowland settlements--

29:38.344 --> 29:41.347
-Oh, aye--
-Aye, go on then, Crown Prince Mary Jane!

29:41.380 --> 29:42.448
Get your fucking sword out!

29:42.481 --> 29:44.016
[George] And by thunderous God,

29:44.049 --> 29:45.818
what makes you think it was us
in your lands?

29:45.851 --> 29:49.388
[Meg] Because the ale had been drunk
and all the sheep were pregnant.

29:49.421 --> 29:53.125
[tolling continues,
horse neighs in the distance]

29:53.159 --> 29:57.396
[James] Ah, hen,
and I told you this was, uh...

29:57.429 --> 29:58.898
men's work.

29:58.931 --> 30:00.266
[Meg] Oh, for the love of God
and all the saints,

30:00.299 --> 30:01.934
you call yourselves men.

30:01.967 --> 30:03.369
My children are better behaved.

30:03.402 --> 30:05.571
Your Grace, what's a woman doing here?

30:05.804 --> 30:09.108
I am your queen,
Alexander Stewart, you pig!

30:09.141 --> 30:10.543
[George]
Your Grace, this is a clan meeting.

30:10.576 --> 30:13.012
We can't see it
turned into a sewing circle.

30:13.045 --> 30:15.214
Please, Father, let us not stoop
to humiliating the wife of our king--

30:15.247 --> 30:16.949
[Gavin] You shut your face, Angus.

30:16.982 --> 30:20.019
She's English, and the English
are the cause of all our troubles.

30:20.052 --> 30:21.387
-[Alexander] True, true.
-[murmuring]

30:21.420 --> 30:22.821
Cannae trust the English

30:22.855 --> 30:25.024
nae more than a randy Douglas
in a sheep pen!

30:25.057 --> 30:26.425
[laughter]

30:26.458 --> 30:28.594
[Meg] My lord...

30:28.827 --> 30:31.397
perhaps you would like
to discipline the nobles

30:31.430 --> 30:35.167
that would insult your queen
so spitefully.

30:35.201 --> 30:38.304
[James] Aye, how should I?

30:38.337 --> 30:41.941
How about one Douglas, one Stewart,
hung, drawn, and quartered?

30:41.974 --> 30:44.210
-[laughter]
-[man] Ooh!

30:44.243 --> 30:48.047
Ah, but look what you have achieved,

30:48.080 --> 30:50.082
my bonnie love.

30:50.115 --> 30:54.253
The clans united as neither
Robert the Bruce

30:54.286 --> 30:56.322
nor William Wallace could've hoped for,

30:56.355 --> 30:59.425
and all because of their contempt
for the English.

30:59.458 --> 31:02.228
[laughter]

31:02.261 --> 31:05.264
[mugs clinking]

31:05.297 --> 31:10.202
♪ ♪

31:10.236 --> 31:13.372
[horse neighs in the distance]

31:15.174 --> 31:17.576
[James] Well...

31:17.610 --> 31:20.179
[grunts]

31:20.212 --> 31:24.116
Well, she may not punch like a Stewart,
but she could well pass for a Douglas.

31:24.149 --> 31:27.119
[laughter]

31:27.152 --> 31:30.122
[dramatic music]

31:30.155 --> 31:33.559
♪ ♪

31:33.592 --> 31:35.628
[in Spanish]
My beautiful angel...

31:35.661 --> 31:37.896
...I write to you with a heavy heart.

31:41.166 --> 31:45.004
We wait upon the cold, wet fields
of San Sebastian.

31:45.037 --> 31:49.441
We wait and wait,
but my Spanish brothers do not come.

31:49.475 --> 31:50.976
[in English]
Fuck.

31:52.177 --> 31:54.513
[in Spanish]
Some of my own men leave me...

31:55.281 --> 31:59.952
...risking the noose rather than rot
in these cold, empty lands.

32:00.919 --> 32:03.455
Where is King Ferdinand?

32:03.656 --> 32:08.627
♪ ♪

32:08.661 --> 32:11.664
[baby fusses]

32:13.332 --> 32:14.633
Highness.

32:16.368 --> 32:18.003
[Lina] Oviedo writes to me.

32:18.037 --> 32:20.572
He says the Tudor army wait,

32:20.606 --> 32:23.142
and yet your father's army does not come.

32:23.175 --> 32:25.377
[Catherine] Oh, he's on his way.

32:25.411 --> 32:28.180
He wrote to me that bad weather
delayed them.

32:31.383 --> 32:33.986
Do you know how far away he is?

32:34.019 --> 32:37.389
It will light the spirits of the men
if I can share this with them.

32:37.423 --> 32:39.258
[chuckles]

32:39.291 --> 32:42.995
He will reach them
long before your letter gets there.

32:43.028 --> 32:45.631
The spring has been too wet,

32:45.664 --> 32:48.567
but now the summer comes,
the ground is dry,

32:48.600 --> 32:50.669
the horses fast, and the men sure-footed.

32:50.703 --> 32:53.472
But forgive me, Highness.

32:53.505 --> 32:55.641
This was not what was agreed.

32:55.674 --> 32:57.710
You know yourself he can play tricks.

32:57.743 --> 33:00.045
[Catherine]
Lina, I have told you he is coming.

33:01.046 --> 33:02.981
Be satisfied with it.

33:04.249 --> 33:07.219
[moody music]

33:07.252 --> 33:12.257
♪ ♪

33:12.624 --> 33:15.160
[in Spanish]
My love, my husband.

33:15.194 --> 33:17.529
You are not forsaken.

33:17.563 --> 33:20.299
Not by your King nor your Queen.

33:21.033 --> 33:24.336
They wait for better weather, that is all.

33:27.673 --> 33:30.609
And I send you joyful news...

33:31.243 --> 33:35.214
♪ ♪

33:35.647 --> 33:41.153
...I am with child,
and you will be a father.

33:41.186 --> 33:43.322
He waits as you do.

33:44.623 --> 33:47.393
How a child will bless us

33:47.426 --> 33:49.261
and give us joy!

33:52.598 --> 33:55.067
How strange and wonderful
that seems to me.

33:57.169 --> 34:00.572
Win your war, my brave man...

34:01.340 --> 34:03.742
...and come home to me...

34:03.776 --> 34:05.077
to us.

34:07.179 --> 34:10.182
[bell tolling]

34:19.758 --> 34:22.661
[door opens, closes]

34:29.701 --> 34:31.637
[in English]
Maggie.

34:31.670 --> 34:33.372
Your Grace.

34:35.140 --> 34:36.642
[door closes]

34:36.675 --> 34:40.813
Hold out your hands
with the palms facing up.

34:42.147 --> 34:44.216
I do not understand.

34:44.249 --> 34:47.152
Today marks the anniversary
of the death of Sir Richard.

34:48.420 --> 34:50.489
We do not forget,

34:50.522 --> 34:52.624
myself and the King.

34:52.658 --> 34:55.828
[breathes deeply]

34:58.197 --> 35:00.299
This is for sorrow.

35:00.332 --> 35:04.636
♪ ♪

35:04.670 --> 35:06.705
This is for healing.

35:06.738 --> 35:08.774
♪ ♪

35:08.807 --> 35:11.410
When you pray for your husband's soul,

35:11.443 --> 35:13.545
hold one in each hand.

35:14.613 --> 35:16.682
Squeeze them tightly.

35:18.283 --> 35:19.351
I will.

35:20.786 --> 35:22.421
Thank you.

35:24.122 --> 35:26.525
How are the children?

35:26.558 --> 35:27.826
Has Reggie...

35:27.860 --> 35:30.796
He still does not speak to me.

35:30.829 --> 35:33.131
♪ ♪

35:33.165 --> 35:35.267
Then the healing is for Reggie also.

35:35.300 --> 35:39.238
♪ ♪

35:39.271 --> 35:41.773
Catherine...

35:41.807 --> 35:44.142
thank you.

35:44.176 --> 35:49.181
♪ ♪

35:55.888 --> 35:58.290
Your Grace, a letter for you.

35:58.323 --> 35:59.725
It has your father's seal.

35:59.758 --> 36:00.926
Here, I'll take him.

36:01.159 --> 36:04.162
[baby fussing]

36:15.173 --> 36:17.609
Have they met the English army?

36:19.678 --> 36:21.280
Fetch my clothes.

36:21.313 --> 36:22.614
I will see the King.

36:24.483 --> 36:26.552
[whispering] Do you think we lost the war?

36:26.585 --> 36:29.221
[dramatic music]

36:29.254 --> 36:33.725
♪ ♪

36:33.759 --> 36:35.294
[indistinct chatter]

36:37.229 --> 36:39.598
[Catherine] Leave us.

36:39.631 --> 36:41.567
Um, please go.

36:41.600 --> 36:45.437
♪ ♪

36:48.540 --> 36:50.576
-What is it?
-[door closes]

36:50.609 --> 36:52.578
He is not coming.

36:52.611 --> 36:55.480
My father,
he has taken his army to Navarre,

36:55.514 --> 36:57.249
200 miles to the south,

36:57.282 --> 36:58.750
to reclaim his lands there
from the French.

36:58.784 --> 37:01.653
Why... why would he do that?

37:01.687 --> 37:03.655
[Catherine] He has used us as a decoy

37:03.689 --> 37:06.525
to draw the French,
leaving Navarre open for him to take.

37:07.693 --> 37:09.628
He has betrayed us, Henry.

37:15.801 --> 37:18.503
The alliance was a lie.

37:18.537 --> 37:21.006
I am sorry that I...

37:21.239 --> 37:22.240
trusted him.

37:22.274 --> 37:23.575
He...

37:23.609 --> 37:25.677
has humiliated both of us.

37:27.646 --> 37:30.482
-It is my fault.
-[pounds table]

37:32.551 --> 37:34.653
[in Spanish]
Don't worry, we will play again.

37:34.686 --> 37:39.625
♪ ♪

37:42.894 --> 37:43.895
Take it.

37:43.929 --> 37:48.934
♪ ♪

37:48.967 --> 37:52.437
[exhales sharply]

37:54.039 --> 37:55.974
[Henry] We have been betrayed.

37:57.542 --> 38:00.712
Two hundred thousand ducats wasted.

38:02.981 --> 38:05.951
Two thousand soldiers dead

38:05.984 --> 38:08.587
from hunger or disease.

38:08.620 --> 38:11.790
"Tricky as a fox"...

38:11.823 --> 38:14.459
turned out to be true.

38:14.493 --> 38:16.361
Bring our men home now.

38:18.630 --> 38:20.599
I apologize to this council.

38:20.632 --> 38:24.336
Your Grace, you must not blame yourself.

38:24.369 --> 38:26.304
[Catherine]
I believed my father's sincerity,

38:26.338 --> 38:28.340
but he betrayed us.

38:28.373 --> 38:30.075
Not the Spanish.

38:30.308 --> 38:31.443
Him alone.

38:31.476 --> 38:33.845
The shame is not our queen's.

38:33.879 --> 38:38.350
She did what any dutiful daughter
would've done...

38:38.383 --> 38:40.719
but her father is a lying bastard!

38:42.320 --> 38:44.022
[Walpole] Council is adjourned.

38:47.426 --> 38:48.927
[Catherine] Henry!

38:55.634 --> 38:58.003
The King's mood will settle.

38:58.036 --> 39:01.606
I will arrange a stag hunt for him.
He needs to burn this off.

39:01.640 --> 39:04.976
We have worked so hard together
to build this...

39:05.010 --> 39:06.011
this...

39:06.044 --> 39:07.713
Camelot, yes.

39:10.348 --> 39:13.485
You and the King are young...

39:13.518 --> 39:14.953
idealistic.

39:14.986 --> 39:17.456
But he must shake the glister
of youth from his eyes

39:17.489 --> 39:20.625
and be a man and king for England,

39:20.659 --> 39:24.963
and you must do what England loves you for

39:24.996 --> 39:27.799
and radiate your light

39:27.833 --> 39:31.403
and your beauty and your kindness.

39:31.436 --> 39:34.406
[somber string music]

39:34.439 --> 39:39.444
♪ ♪

39:43.782 --> 39:46.918
I tried to warn you
about your father, Highness,

39:46.952 --> 39:51.590
but now the English people say we Spanish
are all the same,

39:51.623 --> 39:52.891
just like him,

39:52.924 --> 39:55.627
and we cannot be trusted.

39:55.660 --> 39:58.430
All of us must live with this,
not only you.

40:00.966 --> 40:03.001
The thought makes you faint, does it?

40:03.034 --> 40:05.537
Lina, is it the baby?

40:06.705 --> 40:08.073
Baby?

40:10.642 --> 40:13.845
[Lina] Bessie, would you fetch some ale

40:13.879 --> 40:15.647
for the Queen?

40:23.989 --> 40:27.192
[baby fussing]

40:27.425 --> 40:28.827
You...

40:30.495 --> 40:32.964
...are with child?

40:32.998 --> 40:35.433
Yes, Highness.

40:35.467 --> 40:36.601
How long?

40:36.635 --> 40:38.804
I think...

40:38.837 --> 40:40.972
three months.

40:41.006 --> 40:42.941
But you didn't tell me.

40:42.974 --> 40:44.976
I did not want to tell you when...

40:45.010 --> 40:47.679
you had so much to occupy your mind.

40:51.116 --> 40:52.884
My father...

40:52.918 --> 40:55.821
he took the grape.

40:55.854 --> 40:58.657
He used to promise me that this time,
he'd let me take it.

40:58.690 --> 41:00.458
[scoffs]

41:00.492 --> 41:02.027
Then he'd do it again...

41:03.528 --> 41:05.530
...and again.

41:05.564 --> 41:07.165
Now again.

41:09.467 --> 41:11.570
Have I become like him...

41:13.738 --> 41:16.107
...so you no longer trust me?

41:16.141 --> 41:19.144
Am I so changed
that we are no longer friends?

41:19.177 --> 41:22.581
That is your choice, Catherine.

41:22.614 --> 41:26.251
You are the Queen. I am your lady.

41:26.484 --> 41:28.820
Whether or not we are friends

41:28.854 --> 41:31.823
is in your gift, not mine.

41:33.558 --> 41:37.162
This place, the palace...

41:37.195 --> 41:39.865
it is not a home.

41:39.898 --> 41:42.868
It is like a gaming board,

41:42.901 --> 41:45.604
and they all play the games.

41:45.637 --> 41:47.072
You too.

41:48.506 --> 41:51.042
You play them very well.

41:51.076 --> 41:54.713
But I do not wish to play.

41:54.746 --> 41:57.749
I merely wish to live my simple life.

42:05.123 --> 42:07.092
I am happy for you, Lina.

42:11.630 --> 42:13.198
Go.

42:13.231 --> 42:15.233
You should rest.

42:15.267 --> 42:16.935
When you are fuller in your term,

42:16.968 --> 42:19.137
you may stay home
until you are ready to return to me...

42:19.170 --> 42:21.606
[somber music]

42:21.640 --> 42:23.275
...for your child's sake.

42:23.308 --> 42:25.243
♪ ♪

42:25.277 --> 42:27.145
You are better than your father.

42:28.546 --> 42:30.315
You show strength

42:30.548 --> 42:32.117
but humility...

42:33.652 --> 42:36.254
...courage and patience.

42:38.189 --> 42:42.160
And you do something
your mother and father could not do.

42:42.193 --> 42:46.965
You ask questions of others
as well as handing them orders.

42:48.867 --> 42:51.803
You have a good heart, Catherine.

42:53.138 --> 42:55.573
This storm will pass.

42:55.607 --> 43:00.612
♪ ♪

43:16.161 --> 43:17.662
Henry...

43:20.165 --> 43:22.334
...may I attend your bed tonight?

43:25.637 --> 43:26.972
I'm tired.

43:27.005 --> 43:29.975
[melancholy music]

43:30.008 --> 43:35.013
♪ ♪

43:38.984 --> 43:40.852
Good night, Your Grace.

43:40.885 --> 43:45.890
♪ ♪

44:09.247 --> 44:11.850
Well, that was a bollocking waste of time.

44:11.883 --> 44:13.718
[Henry] General Howard...

44:13.752 --> 44:15.253
my lord Stafford...

44:19.324 --> 44:21.359
...good men of England...

44:26.097 --> 44:27.399
...we are sorry.

44:29.000 --> 44:32.971
You brave men did not deserve
to languish in such ignominy.

44:33.004 --> 44:35.106
King Ferdinand...

44:37.876 --> 44:40.045
King Ferdinand betrayed you...

44:40.078 --> 44:41.212
and me, too.

44:41.246 --> 44:44.149
[Henry] But you did not betray yourselves.

44:44.182 --> 44:46.684
Captain Oviedo, step forward.

44:48.887 --> 44:50.321
Your Grace.

44:50.355 --> 44:53.391
[Henry] We're told you worked
tirelessly to maintain morale,

44:53.425 --> 44:55.427
that you even brought back
some who deserted.

44:57.729 --> 45:01.266
The Queen wishes to bestow
a gift upon you.

45:04.769 --> 45:06.137
Oviedo of Maceta,

45:06.171 --> 45:09.140
for your service to England,
we make you a commoner knight.

45:10.442 --> 45:13.778
Receive the title knight banneret...

45:13.812 --> 45:15.013
with our gratitude.

45:17.282 --> 45:20.085
[Henry] Think of it as a personal apology

45:20.118 --> 45:21.820
on behalf of her country.

45:23.288 --> 45:27.125
I think of this as a blessing
from my queen.

45:31.763 --> 45:32.864
I'm going hunting.

45:39.804 --> 45:42.040
[footsteps approaching]

45:42.073 --> 45:43.942
[sighs]

45:43.975 --> 45:46.111
[baby fusses]

45:46.144 --> 45:49.214
[Catherine] Hello.

45:49.247 --> 45:50.448
[Ursula] He's teething.

45:51.816 --> 45:53.451
I will take him for a while.

45:53.485 --> 45:56.287
[baby cries]

45:56.321 --> 45:57.956
Okay.

45:57.989 --> 45:59.958
[groans happily]

46:01.459 --> 46:03.428
[speaks Spanish]

46:03.461 --> 46:06.431
[dramatic music]

46:06.464 --> 46:09.834
♪ ♪

46:09.868 --> 46:12.837
[baby fussing]

46:12.871 --> 46:17.876
♪ ♪

46:20.478 --> 46:23.014
Come, come.

46:23.047 --> 46:25.450
We will speak to God

46:25.483 --> 46:29.287
and ask Him to forgive your mother's pride

46:29.320 --> 46:31.189
and guide her in the future.

46:33.491 --> 46:35.226
[sniffles] Come on.

46:35.260 --> 46:38.229
[tender music]

46:38.263 --> 46:39.564
♪ ♪

46:39.797 --> 46:42.567
[baby fussing]

46:42.800 --> 46:45.203
♪ ♪

46:45.236 --> 46:46.871
Holy Father...

46:48.973 --> 46:51.342
...forgive me for my sins.

46:51.376 --> 46:53.578
[continues praying indistinctly]

46:53.811 --> 46:56.347
<i>Give me Your wisdom.</i>

46:56.381 --> 46:58.383
<i>Holy Father...</i>

47:00.051 --> 47:01.886
...I was tempted by...

47:03.054 --> 47:05.390
[scoffs] ...by vanity.

47:07.125 --> 47:08.893
I turned away from You.

47:11.262 --> 47:12.864
Holy Father...

47:12.897 --> 47:16.034
♪ ♪

47:16.067 --> 47:18.236
...help my husband.

47:18.269 --> 47:20.238
Heal his heart.

47:20.271 --> 47:25.276
♪ ♪

47:28.146 --> 47:29.347
Henry...

47:29.380 --> 47:32.150
♪ ♪

47:32.183 --> 47:33.585
Henry?

47:33.618 --> 47:36.921
♪ ♪

47:36.955 --> 47:38.623
Henry!

47:38.856 --> 47:40.425
Hen... Henry!

47:40.458 --> 47:42.193
[gasps]

47:42.227 --> 47:43.494
Henry.

47:43.528 --> 47:45.063
<i>Henry!</i>

47:45.096 --> 47:48.066
[mournful music]

47:48.099 --> 47:53.104
♪ ♪

48:12.123 --> 48:15.126
[Catherine whimpering]

48:17.528 --> 48:19.464
[Maggie] Catherine...

48:19.497 --> 48:22.467
[scoffs, crying softly]

48:22.500 --> 48:27.505
♪ ♪

49:04.509 --> 49:06.311
-[door opens]
-[inhales sharply]

49:17.121 --> 49:18.189
Highness.

49:24.195 --> 49:25.263
Catherine...

49:30.535 --> 49:32.537
...the King wishes to see you.

49:42.680 --> 49:45.383
[Catherine sobs softly]

49:47.218 --> 49:49.654
-I have waited for you.
-[door closes]

49:51.489 --> 49:53.291
I know.

49:56.060 --> 49:59.030
I know now what you felt
when your mother died and you...

50:02.667 --> 50:04.068
...you said you could not help

50:04.102 --> 50:07.205
but feel that she was cold
under the ground.

50:10.074 --> 50:12.577
Henry, will he have
enough swaddling around him?

50:14.345 --> 50:17.448
[sobbing]

50:19.417 --> 50:20.485
[Henry] My love...

50:21.786 --> 50:24.655
-...my poor, sweet love.
-[cries]

50:24.689 --> 50:27.258
Why? Why?

50:27.291 --> 50:29.460
Why would God...

50:31.362 --> 50:35.500
Does He punish us? Is this punishment?

50:35.533 --> 50:36.734
Why would He?

50:43.107 --> 50:44.609
I love you, Catherine.

50:46.077 --> 50:48.813
And I will love you and love you,

50:49.046 --> 50:51.249
and we will have another son,

50:51.282 --> 50:55.520
and he will be strong
because we are so strong.

50:57.121 --> 50:59.557
[soft music]

50:59.590 --> 51:02.593
[Catherine gasps] Yes.

51:02.627 --> 51:04.061
Yes.

51:04.095 --> 51:05.830
I cannot lose you.

51:06.063 --> 51:07.732
I cannot lose you, Henry.

51:07.765 --> 51:12.603
♪ ♪

51:28.653 --> 51:31.122
[Meg crying]

51:32.490 --> 51:35.092
[James] My love, I'm sorry.

51:35.126 --> 51:37.361
You, most of all,

51:37.395 --> 51:39.764
will understand Catherine's suffering.

51:39.797 --> 51:43.468
[cries]

51:43.501 --> 51:47.872
Not another child, not another.

51:48.105 --> 51:49.640
Oh, that poor wee boy.

51:51.375 --> 51:52.577
[James] Hey.

51:56.814 --> 51:59.684
If you wish to ride south to see her...

52:04.689 --> 52:07.458
No, I'll stay in Scotland

52:07.492 --> 52:09.193
and do my duty...

52:10.895 --> 52:12.697
...and I'll grieve in private.

52:14.198 --> 52:17.335
You're a fine queen, Meg,

52:17.368 --> 52:19.203
and a good wife.

52:20.404 --> 52:23.307
You'll win the hearts
of Scotland in no time.

52:24.475 --> 52:27.612
When I next see Catherine, I will...

52:27.645 --> 52:29.380
hold her close.

52:30.882 --> 52:34.185
She is <i>hermana...</i>

52:34.218 --> 52:35.353
sister.

52:35.386 --> 52:40.391
♪ ♪

52:59.410 --> 53:01.712
[Lina whispering prayer indistinctly]

53:01.746 --> 53:06.751
♪ ♪

53:24.769 --> 53:27.905
[bell tolling]

53:27.939 --> 53:32.910
♪ ♪

53:38.649 --> 53:40.818
[in Spanish]
To my daughter, Katalina.

53:41.986 --> 53:44.889
I write to you from my new lands
in Navarre,

53:44.922 --> 53:46.891
which I know will twist the knife.

53:47.892 --> 53:51.696
The game of politics and kingship
is a hard one,

53:51.729 --> 53:56.500
and you and your young bull
must learn to play if you would win.

53:56.534 --> 53:58.469
Don't be bitter like the English...

53:59.370 --> 54:01.973
...be proud and brave, Castilian...

54:03.507 --> 54:04.976
...as your mother was.

54:06.010 --> 54:08.846
You are still a child of Spain.

54:09.714 --> 54:11.949
And you are mine.

54:12.717 --> 54:17.722
♪ ♪

54:33.537 --> 54:35.640
[in English]
"Do not be like the English."

54:35.673 --> 54:40.678
♪ ♪

54:42.279 --> 54:43.347
Henry...

54:44.815 --> 54:46.984
...you were right to speak of strength.

54:48.519 --> 54:51.055
We were strong enough
to build this Camelot.

54:51.288 --> 54:53.324
♪ ♪

54:53.357 --> 54:55.960
Now we must be even stronger to keep it.

54:55.993 --> 55:00.998
♪ ♪

55:21.786 --> 55:24.522
[Catherine] Why do I speak...

55:24.555 --> 55:26.891
and not the King?

55:26.924 --> 55:31.562
Because your pain is mine
and I have caused it.

55:33.497 --> 55:36.634
We were children...

55:36.667 --> 55:40.104
but we are not children anymore.

55:40.337 --> 55:42.039
Our innocence is lost.

55:43.741 --> 55:47.511
And our new wisdom forged in pain...

55:47.545 --> 55:49.513
and grief...

55:49.547 --> 55:51.916
and terrible sadness.

55:55.352 --> 55:57.722
We have lost our precious son...

56:00.524 --> 56:03.427
...and we have also lost
our dignity to Spain.

56:04.628 --> 56:07.531
My father wrote to gloat

56:07.565 --> 56:10.601
about his victory,

56:10.634 --> 56:12.937
but I will tell you this...

56:12.970 --> 56:16.073
we do not drown when we feel grief.

56:17.708 --> 56:21.612
We do not shy from our mistakes,

56:21.645 --> 56:26.383
and we do not stand
to be betrayed by allies!

56:29.787 --> 56:32.757
[dramatic music]

56:32.790 --> 56:35.426
We called you here

56:35.459 --> 56:39.163
because the whole of England
must know this.

56:39.396 --> 56:41.665
I am reborn.

56:42.800 --> 56:44.602
I am English!

56:46.570 --> 56:49.006
God save King Henry!

56:49.039 --> 56:53.177
[all] God save the King!
God save the King!

56:53.410 --> 56:56.781
[Oviedo] God save
Queen Catherine of England!

56:56.814 --> 56:58.849
[all] God save the Queen!

56:58.883 --> 57:03.587
God save the Queen! God save the Queen!

57:03.621 --> 57:05.689
God save the Queen!

57:05.723 --> 57:08.926
-[chanting continues]
-We will go to war with France...

57:08.959 --> 57:10.561
but this time on our own.

57:10.594 --> 57:15.432
[crowd] God save the Queen!
God save the Queen!

57:15.466 --> 57:19.003
[Catherine]
England, you shall have your victory,

57:19.036 --> 57:23.174
and you will also have
a new heir from my womb.

57:23.207 --> 57:26.043
♪ ♪

57:26.076 --> 57:29.980
I stand here as a daughter of England,
and I make you that promise.

57:30.014 --> 57:34.652
[crowd] God save the Queen!
God save the Queen!

57:34.685 --> 57:39.690
♪ ♪
